      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "n = gets.to_i\ngrid = []\n\nn.times do\n  row = gets.split\n  grid << row\nend\n\noptions = [*0...n].permutation(n)\n\nsolution = options.find{|list|\n  list.each_cons(2).all?{|a, b| (a-b).abs > 1 } &&\n    list.map.with_index{|col, row| grid[row][col] }.uniq.size == n\n}\n\nsolution.each_with_index{|col, row| grid[row][col] = \"Q\" }\n\nputs grid.map{|row| row*\" \" }",
      "statement": "The game 'Queens' is played on an [[n]]x[[n]] board.\n\nThe board has [[n]] different 'colours' depicted as hexadecimal digits ({{0123456789ABCDEF}}).\n\nYou must place [[n]] queens ({{Q}} symbols) on the board, following the below rules:\n\n<<1. >> No two queens can be on the same row or column\n<<2. >> No two queens can be one square apart diagonally\n<<3. >> No two queens can be on the same colour\n\nThere is only one solution for each board. Find it, however you can!",
