    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">The game 'Queens' is played on an <var>n</var>x<var>n</var> board.<br><br>The board has <var>n</var> different 'colours' depicted as hexadecimal digits (<const>0123456789ABCDEF</const>).<br><br>You must place <var>n</var> queens (<const>Q</const> symbols) on the board, following the below rules:<br><br><strong>1. </strong> No two queens can be on the same row or column<br><strong>2. </strong> No two queens can be one square apart diagonally<br><strong>3. </strong> No two queens can be on the same colour<br><br>There is only one solution for each board. Find it, however you can!</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>Line 1 :</strong> <var>n</var>, the number of rows, columns and colours on the board<br><strong>Next <var>n</var> lines :</strong> <var>n</var> space-separated hexadecimal digits representing the colours of that row</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\"><strong><var>n</var> lines :</strong> the same board, now solved, with the symbol <const>Q</const> replacing the squares where queens must be placed</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">7 &le; <var>n</var> &le; 11</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">5\n0 0 1 1 2\n3 0 0 1 2\n3 4 0 2 2\n3 4 0 2 2\n3 3 3 2 2</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-out\">Q 0 1 1 2\n3 0 0 Q 2\n3 Q 0 2 2\n3 4 0 2 Q\n3 3 Q 2 2</pre>\n         </div>\n      </div>\n   </div>\n</div>"
